    "body": "You certainly can issue an 'Attack' order -- manually queueing up\nactivities is fraught with trouble though, since the activities used can\nvary wildly based on what traits the actor has.\n\nPerhaps what we want is a Lua hook into ResolveOrder (so you get the\ncorrect activity dispatch in all cases, given a synthetic order)?\n\nOn Tue, Feb 10, 2015 at 11:38 AM, Bynnar18 notifications@github.com wrote:\n\n> Units that aren't planes don't have a straight attack function. You have\n> to use something like AttackMove.\n> \n> â€”\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub\n> https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA/issues/7453#issuecomment-73606060.\n"
